ATLAS

Ατλας / アトラス
A persistent AI teammate, not a chatbot.

WHAT IS ATLAS?

Atlas is an event-driven AI teammate platform built with:

- Bun (runtime + package manager)
- TypeScript (strict, type aliases only)
- Vercel AI SDK (provider-agnostic via LiteLLM)
- Graphiti + FalkorDB (temporal knowledge graphs for memory)
- PostgreSQL (event persistence, no ORM)
- Redis (cache + pub/sub)
- BullMQ (background jobs)
- OpenTelemetry (traces, metrics, logs — all through one collector)

Platform-agnostic by design. Slack, Discord, and Linear are simply
adapters around the same core engine. The runtime knows nothing about
which platform it serves.

FEATURES

- single runtime across multiple communication platforms
- platform adapters declare capabilities via flags, not type checks
- event-driven architecture — everything is an immutable event
- planner pipeline: observe, retrieve context, plan, execute tools, respond, persist memory
- Graphiti-powered long-term memory with episodic, semantic, and graph layers
- AI provider-agnostic — switch models via configuration only
- OpenTelemetry on every operation — incoming event, model request, tool execution, memory retrieval, database query, outgoing message
- tool registry with output truncation and OTel tracing
- BullMQ parent-child job flows for async AI pipelines
- zero interfaces, zero comments, zero dead code

TECH STACK

Core

- Bun (runtime, package manager, test runner)
- TypeScript (strict, exactOptionalPropertyTypes, noUncheckedIndexedAccess)
- Vercel AI SDK + @ai-sdk/openai (OpenAI-compatible endpoint for LiteLLM)

Data

- PostgreSQL via postgres.js (no ORM, raw SQL, explicit queries)
- Redis via ioredis (cache, pub/sub, BullMQ backend)
- Graphiti REST API + FalkorDB (temporal knowledge graphs)

Infrastructure

- BullMQ (background jobs, rate limiting, parent-child flows)
- OpenTelemetry (manual instrumentation, OTLP HTTP exporter)
- Podman / Docker Compose (local infrastructure)

Platforms

- Slack (Web API via fetch, streaming via message editing)
- Discord (REST API v10, streaming via message editing)
- Linear (GraphQL API, no streaming)

PROJECT STRUCTURE

packages/
├── types/ @atlas/types — domain types, zero deps
├── primitives/ @atlas/primitives — result, async, time, id
├── config/ @atlas/config — Zod-validated env config
├── otel/ @atlas/otel — manual OTel, withSpan, metrics, logs
├── db/ @atlas/db — postgres.js, migrations, traced queries
├── cache/ @atlas/cache — ioredis, traced ops, pub/sub
├── events/ @atlas/events — event bus, PostgreSQL persistence, Redis pub/sub
├── ai/ @atlas/ai — Vercel SDK wrapper, generate, stream, structured, tools
├── memory/ @atlas/memory — Graphiti REST client, episode storage, fact search
├── tools/ @atlas/tools — registry, execution, builtins (search, http, reminder)
├── jobs/ @atlas/jobs — BullMQ queues, workers, enqueue
├── core/ @atlas/core — runtime engine, planner pipeline, session store
└── adapters/
├── slack/ @atlas/slack — Slack platform adapter
├── discord/ @atlas/discord — Discord platform adapter
└── linear/ @atlas/linear — Linear platform adapter

apps/
└── local-dev/ @atlas/local-dev — interactive CLI, wiring, Docker Compose

docs/
└── adr/ 14 architecture decision records

docker/
└── compose.yaml PostgreSQL, Redis, FalkorDB, Graphiti, OTEL Collector

DEVELOPMENT

Install dependencies:

bun install

Copy .env defaults (already present in repo root):

ATLAS_AI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000
ATLAS_AI_API_KEY=sk-placeholder
ATLAS_AI_MODEL=openai/gpt-4o-mini

Start infrastructure (requires podman or docker):

bash compose.sh up -d

Run the local dev CLI:

bun run dev

COMMANDS

bun run dev Start local-dev CLI (interactive, --watch)
bun run build Build all packages (bun build + tsc declarations)
bun run typecheck Typecheck all packages (tsc --noEmit)
bun test Run tests (bun test)
bun run lint Lint with ESLint
bun run format Format with Prettier
bash compose.sh up Start infrastructure (podman or docker)
bash compose.sh down Stop infrastructure

ARCHITECTURE

Platform events flow through a single pipeline:

Slack / Discord / Linear
|
Platform Adapters (normalize events, send responses)
|
Event Bus (immutable events, PostgreSQL persistence, Redis pub/sub)
|
Atlas Runtime (core engine — platform-agnostic)
+--------+----------+-----------+
| | | |
Planner Memory Tool Manager
| | |
+--------+----------+
|
AI Provider (Vercel SDK -> LiteLLM)

The planner pipeline: observe -> retrieve context -> plan ->
execute tools -> generate response -> persist memory.

Every step is traced with OpenTelemetry.

DESIGN PRINCIPLES

- Platform agnostic — core knows nothing about Slack, Discord, or Linear
- Memory first — Graphiti manages episodic, semantic, and graph memory
- Event driven — everything is an immutable event
- Observable by default — every operation emits OTel spans
- Replaceable — every dependency is swappable via configuration
- Type aliases only — no interfaces, no inline types, no utility dumping grounds
- Small focused modules — each package has one clear responsibility
- Composition over inheritance — factory functions, not classes

ARCHITECTURE DECISION RECORDS

All major decisions are documented in docs/adr/:

- 0001 Bun as runtime and package manager
- 0002 Graphiti with FalkorDB for memory
- 0003 BullMQ for background jobs
- 0004 PostgreSQL without an ORM
- 0005 Event bus architecture
- 0006 Platform adapter pattern with capabilities
- 0007 Vercel AI SDK with OpenAI-compatible provider
- 0008 OpenTelemetry for all observability
- 0009 Type aliases only (no interfaces)
- 0010 Graphiti REST API integration approach
- 0011 Package naming and monorepo structure
- 0012 Bun workspaces with isolated linker
- 0013 Manual OTel instrumentation over auto-instrumentation
- 0014 ioredis over Bun native Redis client

